Detailed Description

cvmx_pcsx::_int_reg

PCSX Interrupt Register Note: DBG_SYNC is a edge triggered interrupt. When set it indicates PCS Synchronization state machine in Figure 48-7 state diagram in IEEE Std 802.3-2005 changes state SYNC_ACQUIRED_1 to SYNC_ACQUIRED_2 indicating an invalid code group was received on one of the 4 receive lanes. This interrupt should be always disabled and used only for link problem debugging help.
